WEBVTT

00:01.768 --> 00:03.202
<i> Previously on</i> Empire...
You've got ALS.

00:03.204 --> 00:05.104
Is there anything
on the horizon?

00:05.106 --> 00:07.539
It's not my area,
but I'm gonna reach out.

00:07.541 --> 00:09.708
<i> I'm going after his empire,</i>
<i> and I'm gonna take it.</i>

00:09.710 --> 00:11.844
You know, you're the only one
that could run this company.

00:11.846 --> 00:13.312
RHONDA: <i> What if your
brothers</i> <i> went to war?</i>

00:13.314 --> 00:15.114
They just may kill each other.

00:15.116 --> 00:16.849
(gunshot)

00:16.851 --> 00:18.550
Yo, somebody got shot because
you wanted to ruin my session.

00:18.552 --> 00:20.185
You still worrying about singles

00:20.187 --> 00:21.320
<i> when I'm about to be iconic.</i>

00:21.322 --> 00:22.988
<i> You my girl.</i>

00:22.990 --> 00:24.857
<i> You ain't supposed to be
kissing no damn</i> <i> chick...!</i>

00:24.859 --> 00:26.325
TIANA: <i> Look, you got
a sidepiece,</i> <i> too.</i>

00:26.327 --> 00:27.960
Detective Walker,
good to see you again.

00:27.962 --> 00:29.495
WALKER:
<i> We think Bunkie was shot</i>

00:29.497 --> 00:30.896
<i> around 9:30 on the 12th.</i>

00:30.898 --> 00:32.798
Do you recall
where you were at that time?

00:32.800 --> 00:34.833
We were together at his house
watching the fight.

00:34.835 --> 00:37.002
Will you marry me?
Yes!

00:37.004 --> 00:40.873
I gave you an
anniversary present.

00:41.841 --> 00:44.076
♪ ♪

01:10.904 --> 01:13.272
♪ ♪

01:24.551 --> 01:26.085
Hey.

01:26.087 --> 01:27.786
Thank you for joining me.

01:27.788 --> 01:30.022
You don't look bad, ole head.

01:30.024 --> 01:32.591
(chuckles)
Uh, Lucious?

01:34.127 --> 01:37.129
I'm feeling really nervous
about all of this.

01:37.131 --> 01:39.064
About what?

01:39.066 --> 01:40.365
You left that rose and...

01:40.367 --> 01:44.236
You are a bad boy,
Lucious, you know that?

01:44.238 --> 01:46.705
(laughs)
That rose?

01:48.208 --> 01:51.110
Th-That's not why
I brought you here.

01:53.480 --> 01:55.514
Come on.

01:57.984 --> 02:00.652
We both said some things that we
shouldn't have, all right, so,

02:00.654 --> 02:03.255
let's just squash all of this.
HAKEEM: My video about to drop

02:03.257 --> 02:04.723
in a couple weeks.

02:04.725 --> 02:06.258
Dad thinks it's dope.

02:06.260 --> 02:07.659
Oh, well, remind me

02:07.661 --> 02:10.095
to get both of y'all autographs
after dinner.

02:10.097 --> 02:12.264
(elegant classical music
playing)

02:12.266 --> 02:14.666
What is she doing here?

02:14.668 --> 02:17.136
LUCIOUS:
Have a seat,

02:17.138 --> 02:19.471
please.

02:19.473 --> 02:21.306
Hello, everyone.

02:21.308 --> 02:22.741
Hey, Ma.
Hi, Cookie.

02:22.743 --> 02:23.842
Pumpkin.

02:23.844 --> 02:25.344
Hey, Cookie.
COOKIE: Ooh!

02:25.346 --> 02:27.146
A rose.

02:27.148 --> 02:29.414
LUCIOUS: Everyone, I'm so glad
that you guys can join us.

02:29.416 --> 02:31.783
Baby, get up for a second.
Mm-hmm.

02:31.785 --> 02:34.019
We wanted you to be
the first to know

02:34.021 --> 02:37.789
that I have asked Anika
to be my lovely wife.

02:37.791 --> 02:39.158
Bam. (laughing)

02:39.160 --> 02:42.261
It's an Asscher-cut
Krupp diamond.

02:42.263 --> 02:44.830
It's the same one that Richard
Burton gave Elizabeth Taylor.

02:44.832 --> 02:46.431
It's... huge.

02:46.433 --> 02:47.533
It's gorgeous,
isn't it?

02:47.535 --> 02:49.201
(Anika laughs)

02:49.203 --> 02:51.503
To Dad and Anika.
Congratulations.

02:51.505 --> 02:53.372
Thanks, Dre.
Thank you, Dre.

02:53.374 --> 02:54.706
Congratulations.

02:54.708 --> 02:57.109
(slurping loudly)

02:58.478 --> 03:01.146
So, how did he propose?

03:01.148 --> 03:02.514
Tell us the whole story.

03:02.516 --> 03:06.285
Um, last Wednesday,
I came downstairs,

03:06.287 --> 03:08.453
he opened the doors...

03:08.455 --> 03:09.821
There's champagne, ring,

03:09.823 --> 03:11.857
everything, and

03:11.859 --> 03:14.393
Anthony Hamilton in our
living room, (Lucious laughs)

03:14.395 --> 03:16.028
singing "The Point
of it All."

03:16.030 --> 03:17.663
Oh, it was beautiful.

03:17.665 --> 03:19.965
He flew him in from
London just for me.

03:19.967 --> 03:21.066
Mm. I love you.

03:21.068 --> 03:22.067
HAKEEM: Damn.
I love you, too.

03:22.069 --> 03:23.502
Dad doin' it big.

03:23.504 --> 03:24.870
So let me get this straight.

03:24.872 --> 03:26.371
Last Wednesday,

03:26.373 --> 03:28.907
you come to my house
and give me a rose

03:28.909 --> 03:30.842
after you proposed
to that bitch?

03:30.844 --> 03:32.844
Watch yourself, Cookie. What
rose is she talking about?

03:32.846 --> 03:34.379
COOKIE:
Watch yourself, Lucious.

03:34.381 --> 03:35.914
The rose was
a-a friendly reminder

03:35.916 --> 03:37.249
of where we were yesterday.

03:37.251 --> 03:39.918
That's all it was.

03:41.554 --> 03:43.121
Friendly?!
(gasps)

03:44.257 --> 03:45.924
You think I came here

03:45.926 --> 03:48.660
dressed like this
for a friendly get-together?

03:49.729 --> 03:52.231
You know what?
Why don't you all

03:52.233 --> 03:54.032
enjoy your friendly

03:54.034 --> 03:55.067
little family dinner?

03:55.069 --> 03:56.602
Congratulations.

03:56.604 --> 03:58.170
Oh,

03:58.172 --> 04:01.673
and, Anika, this is an ass.

04:04.544 --> 04:06.144
Congrats, Dad.

04:14.687 --> 04:16.088
♪ You got me goin' ♪

04:16.090 --> 04:18.457
♪<i> Give me my money.</i> ♪

04:18.459 --> 04:20.759
(melody and rhythm continues,
slowly fading)

04:28.101 --> 04:30.769
This is a monster!

04:30.771 --> 04:32.971
You're gonna change the game
with this one, Jamal.

04:32.973 --> 04:34.940
I know, right?
Isn't it great?

04:34.942 --> 04:36.708
I really want to promote
this, though, seriously.

04:36.710 --> 04:38.610
Not even your husband
gonna ignore this one.

04:38.612 --> 04:41.046
You mean Anika's husband?

04:41.048 --> 04:43.715
He ain't paying us
no mind anyway.

04:45.918 --> 04:47.452
(Jamal laughs)
What?

04:47.454 --> 04:48.787
Ma, you a mess.

04:48.789 --> 04:51.223
Why you gonna walk up
in there practically

04:51.225 --> 04:53.258
butt-ass naked
underneath that sable in front

04:53.260 --> 04:55.727
of all of us?
Was I giving you body?

04:55.729 --> 04:57.229
(laughter)

04:57.231 --> 04:59.097
JAMAL: I need your head
completely in the game

04:59.099 --> 05:01.099
right now, so,
let's hit this song.

05:01.101 --> 05:03.101
I'm getting this song
on the charts

05:03.103 --> 05:05.504
with or without
Lucious Lyon.

05:14.280 --> 05:15.814
Hey, Cookie?

05:15.816 --> 05:17.349
Yeah?

05:17.351 --> 05:20.585
Have you noticed
any changes in Jamal lately?

05:20.587 --> 05:22.487
Yeah, he's toughening up.
He's becoming a top.

05:22.489 --> 05:25.490
That's what you got to do
to make it to the top.

05:25.492 --> 05:28.126
(chuckles)

05:28.128 --> 05:30.829
Do you think, um...?

05:30.831 --> 05:34.366
You need to start
preparing yourself.

05:34.368 --> 05:36.001
Fame changes people.

05:36.003 --> 05:38.770
What should I do?

05:38.772 --> 05:41.273
Try not to be all up
in his business, you know?

05:41.275 --> 05:43.308
Make sure you got
your own thing going on.

05:43.310 --> 05:45.377
Well, I do. I'm at
the Culinary Institute,

05:45.379 --> 05:47.012
studying to be a chef.

05:47.014 --> 05:51.049
I hope that cooking school
can keep you plenty busy,

05:51.051 --> 05:55.020
because Jamal is gonna have
less and less time for you.

05:59.559 --> 06:02.327
♪ She do it all night,
she do ♪

06:02.329 --> 06:03.962
♪ She goin' hard right ♪

06:03.964 --> 06:05.997
♪ I see you, baby ♪

06:05.999 --> 06:08.133
♪ She love da spotlight ♪

06:08.135 --> 06:09.301
♪ She do ♪

06:09.303 --> 06:10.802
♪ She make dat thang go ♪

06:10.804 --> 06:14.005
♪ Drip drop,
drip drippity drop ♪

06:14.007 --> 06:17.175
♪ Drip drop ♪
♪ I do my dance like ♪

06:17.177 --> 06:20.679
♪ Drip drop,
drip drippity drop ♪

06:20.681 --> 06:21.847
♪ Drip drop,
drip drippity drop... ♪

06:21.849 --> 06:23.615
(gasping quietly)

06:24.650 --> 06:26.151
♪ Funny how the time flies... ♪

06:26.153 --> 06:28.186
(music fades)

06:28.188 --> 06:30.655
(panting)

06:31.758 --> 06:34.159
I saw that cop going
through my trash.

06:34.161 --> 06:36.561
So if Walker was here,
you already a suspect.

06:36.563 --> 06:38.563
Oh, man, that's
ridiculous.

06:38.565 --> 06:40.732
You know what
I want to do?

06:40.734 --> 06:43.335
I want to have his black ass
thrown off the force.

06:43.337 --> 06:45.036
Yeah, then I start
making those calls,

06:45.038 --> 06:47.939
you gonna look
even more guilty.

06:47.941 --> 06:49.107
Are you?

06:51.778 --> 06:52.744
Am I what?

06:52.746 --> 06:54.246
Don't play stupid.

06:54.248 --> 06:56.715
Did you do it?
Did I do what?

06:56.717 --> 06:58.750
Did you kill Bunkie?

06:59.786 --> 07:03.221
(sighs)

07:03.223 --> 07:06.258
Lucious, I cannot help you

07:06.260 --> 07:08.059
if you don't come clean with me.

07:08.061 --> 07:10.629
(sighs)

07:15.968 --> 07:19.771
(laughing): He showed up at
my house 3:00 in the morning,

07:19.773 --> 07:21.373
talking about
this is an emergency.

07:21.375 --> 07:23.608
He wanted to
shake me down

07:23.610 --> 07:25.877
for three million dollars.

07:25.879 --> 07:29.381
What...
what am I supposed to do?

07:29.383 --> 07:30.882
You're supposed to pay the man!

07:30.884 --> 07:33.118
Pay him for what?
For wasting his life?!

07:33.120 --> 07:35.420
He hated you, man,
he hated me,

07:35.422 --> 07:36.955
'cause we did something
with ourselves.

07:36.957 --> 07:39.124
So, you play God?!
No, he played God

07:39.126 --> 07:42.994
the moment he showed up here
and tried to shake me down!

07:42.996 --> 07:45.964
He chose his fate.

07:45.966 --> 07:50.101
He wasn't the Bunkie
you and me grew up with.

07:50.103 --> 07:51.970
He talked
about tearing this down,

07:51.972 --> 07:53.738
everything I done built?

07:54.740 --> 07:56.608
Everything that we've built--

07:56.610 --> 07:58.243
he was gonna tear it down.

07:58.245 --> 08:00.912
You should have come
to me sooner.

08:00.914 --> 08:02.914
What am I gonna say to you, V?

08:02.916 --> 08:04.850
Look, I'm about to kill Bunkie?

08:04.852 --> 08:07.486
I shot him.

08:12.692 --> 08:15.861
Now, how are we
gonna fix this, man?

08:15.863 --> 08:18.363
I'll tell you
what we gonna do.

08:18.365 --> 08:21.132
First thing we gonna do is
beef up security.

08:21.134 --> 08:23.768
That's first.
I've been talking to a guy

08:23.770 --> 08:25.971
that's supposed to be
the best in the business.

08:25.973 --> 08:29.307
We gonna go to work,

08:29.309 --> 08:31.776
we gonna act like
everything is normal.

08:31.778 --> 08:34.579
And that's how
we gonna work this.

08:53.032 --> 08:54.900
Now you listen me.
I'm not approving

08:54.902 --> 08:56.468
any production cost overruns
this quarter, okay?

08:56.470 --> 08:58.537
Now, the closer
we get to this IPO launch,

08:58.539 --> 08:59.871
the more critical... One second.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.973
...the more critical...
Hey, what the...?

09:03.376 --> 09:04.843
Tell me the truth.

09:04.845 --> 09:06.711
You knew that Lucious killed
Bunkie, and you lied

09:06.713 --> 09:10.181
to protect him, didn't you?
You're supposed to have my back.

09:10.183 --> 09:12.384
Right? That's the deal, right? I don't
know what you're talking about.

09:12.386 --> 09:15.720
I sat there and listened
to you give a false alibi.

09:15.722 --> 09:17.389
That's what I do.

09:17.391 --> 09:19.758
I give my father alibis.

09:20.526 --> 09:23.261
(coughing)

09:23.263 --> 09:25.564
What the hell is wrong
with you, Andre?

09:25.566 --> 09:27.999
Nothing wrong with me.
What's wrong with you?

09:28.001 --> 09:30.335
Hmm?

09:30.337 --> 09:34.439
I cover for him, even when
I don't know what I'm covering.

09:43.349 --> 09:45.283
So, I think the next thing
that needs to happen is

09:45.285 --> 09:47.419
we just need to ex out
the things that are cheesy.

09:47.421 --> 09:49.387
All of this girl
is not working for me.

09:49.389 --> 09:51.957
(phone ringing) I actually...
Oh, hold on one second.

09:51.959 --> 09:54.059
Hey, babe. What's up?

09:54.061 --> 09:58.129
I was right about what happened
with Bunkie, Rhonda.

09:59.131 --> 10:00.799
Oh, okay.

10:00.801 --> 10:04.202
Well, um, I'm so happy
to hear that great news.

10:04.204 --> 10:06.805
Can you go somewhere
you can talk?

10:06.807 --> 10:09.708
No, I can't right now,
but I'm really

10:09.710 --> 10:11.710
glad to hear the great news.

10:11.712 --> 10:14.112
Okay.

10:14.114 --> 10:17.382
Call me back, okay?

10:17.384 --> 10:20.018
Call me back.

10:23.756 --> 10:25.457
Why are you even
listening to Cookie?

10:25.459 --> 10:26.891
She was just being honest.

10:26.893 --> 10:28.293
Michael,
what you want me to do?

10:28.295 --> 10:30.061
You want me to swear
on a stack of Bibles

10:30.063 --> 10:31.730
that I'm never gonna blow up
and leave you behind?

10:31.732 --> 10:34.599
All right, since when
do you talk to me like that?

10:34.601 --> 10:36.835
Listen, all I want
is to make sure

10:36.837 --> 10:38.303
that we're still
each other's priority.

10:38.305 --> 10:40.639
Is that too much to ask?
No, it's not. Come here.

10:40.641 --> 10:42.507
No. Jamal...
Babe, come here, come on.

10:42.509 --> 10:46.277
Come on. Let's go away
for the weekend,

10:46.279 --> 10:48.413
show Cookie how wrong she is.

10:48.415 --> 10:50.315
For real?

10:50.317 --> 10:52.684
You come first.
You know that.

10:52.686 --> 10:55.453
First<i> and</i> second
if we're keeping score.

10:55.455 --> 10:57.422
Why don't we go

10:57.424 --> 10:59.290
to that bed-and-breakfast place
in the Berkshires?

10:59.292 --> 11:00.959
The one that Kenny
and John told us about.

11:00.961 --> 11:03.995
Supposed to be super secluded,
no cell phone, no Internet,

11:03.997 --> 11:07.332
no nothing. just you and I. Babe, I can't
be off the grid like that right now.

11:07.334 --> 11:08.442
Come on, don't get mad,
it's a lot happening

11:08.467 --> 11:09.501
right now. All right,
all right, all right.

11:09.503 --> 11:11.536
Okay, I'm not mad. I'm cool.

11:11.538 --> 11:13.738
Just as long as we're together.

11:16.375 --> 11:19.210
Let's just hit up Fire Island
with R.J. and Taylor.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.914
That sounds cool.

11:26.552 --> 11:29.187
A bad week
just got worse.

11:29.189 --> 11:33.191
Well, sobriety's a journey,
not a destination.

11:33.193 --> 11:35.527
You know,
you commit your life

11:35.529 --> 11:40.632
to another man
and his mission...

11:40.634 --> 11:43.568
You know, I practically
raised that man's kids.

11:43.570 --> 11:46.571
So what's changed?
Why's it getting to you now?

11:46.573 --> 11:49.307
A guy we grew up with
got killed.

11:49.309 --> 11:51.743
I mean, he was like
a brother to us.

11:51.745 --> 11:54.279
He lived for Lucious.

11:55.414 --> 11:57.215
Is that a worthy life?

11:57.217 --> 12:01.686
Waking up every day to
serve another man's needs?

12:01.688 --> 12:04.689
If it's time to move on,

12:04.691 --> 12:06.891
maybe it's time.

12:10.196 --> 12:12.731
JAMAL: ♪ I don't need it,
you can keep ya money ♪

12:12.733 --> 12:14.999
♪ I don't want it ♪

12:15.001 --> 12:16.668
♪ If ya gonna
throw it up in my face ♪

12:16.670 --> 12:17.902
♪ I'm still leavin' ♪

12:17.904 --> 12:19.738
♪ You can keep ya money ♪

12:19.740 --> 12:21.506
♪ Because you ain't
worth the time ♪

12:21.508 --> 12:23.508
♪ Can't let it go to waste ♪

12:23.510 --> 12:24.909
♪<i> Money...</i> ♪

12:24.911 --> 12:26.911
Now, that was hot.

12:26.913 --> 12:28.246
Yeah, he's killing it.

12:28.248 --> 12:29.848
I'm so proud of him.

12:29.850 --> 12:32.684
When can I hear
a finished version, Cookie?

12:32.686 --> 12:36.221
The song's already
finished, Miss Calhoun.

12:36.223 --> 12:37.856
Oh, I assumed it was a demo.

12:37.858 --> 12:39.724
You would, because
you're a hater.

12:39.726 --> 12:41.059
See, this is the problem...
Uh, sorry to interrupt.

12:41.061 --> 12:42.360
Just needed to remind
your department

12:42.362 --> 12:44.395
about the new IPO mandate of

12:44.397 --> 12:45.930
cutting fat from
the artist roster.

12:45.932 --> 12:47.565
We're on it.
Um, we are dropping

12:47.567 --> 12:49.067
Alonzo Hall,

12:49.069 --> 12:51.136
Elle Dallas is going and
the Shadow Brothers as well.

12:51.138 --> 12:53.371
Wait, wait, you're
cutting Elle Dallas?

12:53.373 --> 12:56.307
Yes, we are. That's the
dumbest thing I ever heard.

12:56.309 --> 12:58.810
Empire can't cut Elle Dallas.

12:58.812 --> 13:01.613
She is Empire royalty.

13:01.615 --> 13:04.816
Yeah, well, maybe she was,
back in your day, but...

13:04.818 --> 13:07.452
Mom, she's costing
Empire a fortune.

13:07.454 --> 13:09.788
We haven't seen a new revenue
stream from her in years.

13:09.790 --> 13:10.955
And she is difficult.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.124
Yeah, difficult.
I know that word.

13:13.126 --> 13:15.794
You see, y'all like
to toss us to the side

13:15.796 --> 13:17.796
when you can't
control us anymore

13:17.798 --> 13:21.332
because you're lazy and you
don't want to do your job.

13:21.334 --> 13:24.068
Well, just because you don't
know what to do with an A-lister

13:24.070 --> 13:26.004
doesn't mean we toss her
from the label.

13:26.006 --> 13:29.340
No, there is no "we", Cookie.
This is my lane. Mine.

13:29.342 --> 13:31.142
Okay.

13:32.778 --> 13:35.346
COOKIE:
<i> You know the song is good.</i>

13:35.348 --> 13:37.615
You mean the three-and-a-
half-minute piece of crap

13:37.617 --> 13:39.651
that he keeps telling me
to kiss his ass?

13:39.653 --> 13:41.953
(laughs) Yeah, that's song.
It's not funny.

13:41.955 --> 13:43.688
Look, it's going to be a hit.

13:43.690 --> 13:45.423
That's all that matters.

13:45.425 --> 13:48.026
What matters is the fact that
I came down here personally

13:48.028 --> 13:50.662
to introduce you to Elle Dallas,

13:50.664 --> 13:53.865
and all you can do is jam
Jamal down my throat?

13:53.867 --> 13:56.434
Like he said in his song--
keep your money?

13:56.436 --> 13:58.269
That's what I'm gonna do--
I'm gonna keep my money.

13:58.271 --> 14:01.472
Yeah. Well, the only reason
why you're giving me Elle

14:01.474 --> 14:03.041
is because you feel guilty

14:03.043 --> 14:05.210
about leading me on with
the damn rose.  No.

14:05.212 --> 14:07.478
No, you misunderstood the rose.
Oh, man, please.

14:07.480 --> 14:09.547
But I can't wait till
Elle is in your hands,

14:09.549 --> 14:11.482
'cause you gonna have
your hands filled.

14:11.484 --> 14:13.551
Anika thinks
she's hopeless.

14:13.553 --> 14:16.554
Elle's music gave me
a reason to stay alive

14:16.556 --> 14:18.156
when everything else
was telling me

14:18.158 --> 14:21.025
to just give up and... die.

14:21.027 --> 14:23.161
No, she got anger,
you know, that anger

14:23.163 --> 14:25.330
that makes you just
want to fight.

14:25.332 --> 14:26.397
That's...
Well, here she comes.

14:26.399 --> 14:27.732
Oh, my God.

14:29.034 --> 14:31.169
LUCIOUS: Maybe you
can return the favor,

14:31.171 --> 14:34.239
because she needs
the life-saver now.

14:34.241 --> 14:36.374
Elle.

14:36.376 --> 14:38.343
Lucious.
Look at you.

14:38.345 --> 14:40.078
ELLE:
Doll, good to see you.

14:40.080 --> 14:41.479
Hi. Elle.

14:41.481 --> 14:43.047
